comm-1-answer: As an Junglebet Affiliate, you set the commission share percentage for each code you create. This rate indicates the portion of the commission earned from a user's activity that will be returned to them.
comm-2-answer: Once set, this rate is both unchangeable and visible to users. It allows potential referrals to understand their expected returns from wagering under your affiliate code.
comm-3-answer: Commission = (House Edge × Total Wagered by User) × Your Commission %
comm-4-answer: Earnings = (Commission Earned from User) × (Your Set Commission Share %)
comm-5-answer: You set a 20% commission share rate for your code. If a user wagers enough to generate $100 in commission from their activities, they would receive $20 back (20% of $100) due to the rate you set.
comm-6-answer: The commission share rate is crucial in attracting and retaining users. Choose thoughtfully, as it impacts your referrals and subsequent earnings.
